<HEADLINE> Chernomyrdin Meets IOC President </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
MOSCOW, January 16 (Xinhua) -- Visiting International Olympic
Committee (IOC) President Juan Antonio Samaranch Friday expressed
satisfaction with the Russian government's efforts to encourage
sports.
</P>
<P>
During a meeting with Russian Prime Minister Viktor
Chernomyrdin, Samaranch praised the active cooperation of Russia
with its sports organizations, including the National Olympic
Committee, reported the Itar-Tass news agency.
</P>
<P>
Samaranch, who was re-elected in September last year for a
fourth and final term at the age of 77, has asked to finish his
final term in 2001 in Moscow where he was first elected in
1980. The IOC has decided to hold its session in Moscow that
year to accommodate the president's wishes.
</P>
<P>
The Russian premier told Samaranch of his regrets over
St. Petersburg's failure to become the site of the 2004 summer
Olympics. But St. Petersburg may repeat its application to become
the host city for the 2012 games, said the premier.
</P>
<P>
Samaranch arrived in Moscow Thursday for a traditional
Olympic athletes' ball. 
</P>
</TEXT>
