<HEADLINE> French Communist Party Intends to Be "Pole of </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
PARIS, January 16 (Xinhua) -- National Secretary of the French
Communist Party (PCF) Robert Hue said today that the PCF intends
to become "a pole of social success" to push the Socialist
government to respond to the demands of the people.
</P>
<P>
During a meeting with the press, Hue said that the PCF has "a
vaster ambition" than being the "itching powder" or the "prickle"
of the leftwing majority, and instead it wants to "create the
condition for the success of change."
</P>
<P>
"We will work for the success of the majority... and play a
constructive role. The PCF is determined to do its best in playing
this role during the year 1998," he said.
</P>
<P>
He said that with the arrival of "a new phase of national life"
after the leftwing came to power in June 1997, the PCF, which has
joined the government for the first time since 1981, is the
intermediary between the government and social movements.
</P>
<P>
He again called on the government to raise the minimum social
welfare aid, which he described as "an agonizing social
emergency."
</P>
<P>
He described as insufficient the recent offer of 1 billion
francs (166 million U.S. dollars) by Prime Minister Lionel Jospin
to the unemployed, but expressed his confidence in the prime
minister's "capability to understand." 
</P>
</TEXT>
