<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Angolan Govt Strives for Industrial Zone </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
LUANDA, January 16 (Xinhua) -- The central government of
Angola and the local governments are decided to join hands in
building an industrial zone near the capital city.
</P>
<P>
An agreement signed today by the Ministry of Industry and the
Luanda Provincial government said they would contribute their
efforts to the construction of the Viana Industrial Zone about 20
km south of Luanda.
</P>
<P>
The zone, covering an area of 6,000 hectares, is designed to
be a well-equipped industrial satellite city.
</P>
<P>
The central government is to pool 75 million U.S. Dollars in
building the basic infrastructures like roads, sanitation
systems, garbage centers, power plants to attract foreign
investors.
</P>
<P>
The agreement call on both the central and local governments
to take common measures for the industrial zone, saying that
while the provincial government is to guarantee to provide land
for the zone, the central government would take the
responsibility to collect money for its construction.
</P>
<P>
The two sides will set up a committee to work out plans for
the take-off of the project and the construction of the
industrial zone is to start in about six months. 
</P>
</TEXT>
