<HEADLINE> Price of Mealie-Meal Goes up in Zimbabwe </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
HARARE, January 16 (Xinhua) -- The price of mealie-meal,
Zimbabwe's staple food, will go up by 21 percent Monday, the
third increase in two and a half months, a senior official said
today.
</P>
<P>
National Foods Managing Director Ian Kind told the Zimbabwe
News Agency that the recent increase was prompted by the drying
up of maize sources, forcing the grain marketing board to release
maize to millers from the strategic grain reserve.
</P>
<P>
The price of mealie-meal or maize flour has gone up by 60
percent in the past two months while the prices of other basic
commodities have also risen by an average 20 percent since the
beginning of the new year. 
</P>
</TEXT>
