<HEADLINE> EU to Fund Cambodia Elections </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BRUSSELS, January 16 (Xinhua) -- The European Union today said
that it would contribute 9.5 million ECUs (10.5 million U.S.
dollars) to the preparation and implementation of elections in
Cambodia.
</P>
<P>
The money will be used to train Cambodian election officials,
to provide independent observers to the electoral process, and to
train local journalists to ensure valid coverage of all opinions.
</P>
<P>
But the 15-nation union has reserved the right to suspend these
activities if other key factors that would permit free and fair
elections are not put into place.
</P>
<P>
The EU has contributed to the electoral processes in South
Africa in 1994, in Palestine in 1996 and in Bosnia-Herzegovina in
1997.
</P>
<P>
Since the signing of the Paris Peace Accords in October 1991,
the EU has sought to support the reconstruction process in
Cambodia.
</P>
<P>
Financial, technical and humanitarian assistance worth over 170
million ECUs has been channeled into such priority areas as
agriculture, education, health, the environment and institution
building in the Asian country. 
