<P>
He predicted positive changes in the areas of health,
education, employment and some other sectors of the economy.
</P>
<P>
He emphasized the need for a dialog, collective responsibility
and vision among all stakeholders so that the country can gain
its expected economic growth.
</P>
<P>
Investors' confidence is growing steadly and 119 licences were
issued to invstors last year with pleged investments totalling
156 million U.S. dollars, he said.
</P>
<P>
Chiluba said his country has enomous economic potential but
only good management and infrastructure will attract investors to
tap the potential.
</P>
<P>
He said Zambia will continue to encourage private economy and
the market economy will be irreversible in his country.
</P>
<P>
Chiluba said Zambia welcomes all investments. 
</P>
</TEXT>
