<HEADLINE> British Investment in Nigeria Hits 3.48 Billion </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
LAGOS, January 16 (Xinhua) -- British investment in Nigeria
has amounted to 3.48 billion U.S. dollars, the British High
Commission (embassy) said today.
</P>
<P>
The figure comes from a recent survey of 39 major companies
with significant amount of British interest, according to the
current edition of "The Trade", a British embassy publication.
</P>
<P>
Only companies each with a turnover of one million dollars are
incorporated in the survey, it said.
</P>
<P>
Among the 39 companies, 22 are quoted and 17 are private ones,
with those engaged in the field of oil and gas having the highest
level of British interest at 60 percent.
</P>
<P>
According to the publication, the combined market
capitalization of British interest represented by the shares of
the 22 listed companies on the Nigerian stock exchange stands at
570 million dollars, accounting for about 13.2 percent of the
total in the bourse. 
