<HEADLINE> Four Soldiers Sentenced to Death in Rwanda </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
NAIROBI, January 16 (Xinhua) -- The military high court,
sitting in Gitarama, central Rwanda, has sentenced four army
soldiers to death today, according to Rwanda News Agency.
</P>
<P>
The four, all privates, were charged with the murder of a
former Rwandan government officer, Captain Theoreste
Hategekimana, in October 1997.
</P>
<P>
At the time of his murder, Captain Hategekimana was commanding
the Gilarama-Kibuye Gendarmerie Brigade.
</P>
<P>
The four soldiers ambushed his vehicle at Kabgayi, 5 kms south
of Gitarama, on the Kigali-Butare road, killing him and his
escort.
</P>
<P>
Security forces had then arrested the murderers as well as
four army officers on suspicion that the latter were the real
masterminds while the soldiers were executants.
</P>
<P>
In their defense, the four officers rejected charges
connecting them with the assassination of their colleague, while
the soldiers claimed they killed an enemy. 
</P>
