<HEADLINE> Greek Actor Dies </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
ATHENS, January 16 (Xinhua) -- Dimitris Horn, one of Greece's
most celebrated stage and film actors, died here today from heart
attack, at the age of 77.
</P>
<P>
Horn, born in 1921 and the son of well-known playwright
Pantelis Horn, studied drama at the Greek national theater's drama
school from 1937 to 1940, the semi-official Athens News Agency
(ANA) reported.
</P>
<P>
In 1974, he became director of the state-run Greek Radio and
Television Organization, and established the Goulandris-Horn
Foundation for the study of Greek civilization in 1980.
</P>
<P>
He had done perfect performances in the dramas such as
Shakespeare's "Twelfth Night" and "Richard III," and his Greek
cinema credits include Michael Cacoyiannis' "Sunday Awakening" and
"The Girl in Black." 
