<HEADLINE> France, Russia Sign Military Cooperation Agreement </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
PARIS, January 17 (Xinhua) -- France and Russia signed an
agreement on military cooperation Saturday for the 1998-99 period,
said French Defense Minister Alain Richard.
</P>
<P>
The agreement was signed at the end of a three-day visit to
Paris by Russian Defense Minister Igor Sergeyev, the first visit
to France by a Russian defense minister in four years.
</P>
<P>
Agence France-Presse (AFP) said the defense minister's visit has
greatly improved the level of military cooperation between the two
countries.
</P>
<P>
Under the agreement, Russia and France will consult with each
other on a regular basis on strategic and security issues. They
will also exchange high-level military and civil officials to
study each other's reform and modernization of defense forces.
</P>
<P>
Both will also carry out industrial and technological
cooperation in aeronautics and aero-space fields, including
developing the bi-reactor Mig-AT training aircraft and the Future
Transport Aircraft which are being financed by eight European
countries.
</P>
<P>
The agreement also stipulates that joint military exercises be
held in and between the two countries. 
</P>
</TEXT>
