<HEADLINE> Explosion in Mine Kills 29 in Serbia </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BELGRADE, January 17 (Xinhua) -- A methane gas explosion in a
coal mine in Sokobanja, eastern Serbia, killed 29 miners and
injured 19, Tanjug news agency reported.
</P>
<P>
Twenty-eight miners escaped without injury from the disaster,
which occurred late Friday in the Soko lignite mine in Citluk near
Sokobanja.
</P>
<P>
The injured, none of which were in critical condition, were
hospitalized by mid-night, said the report.
</P>
<P>
In 1974, 15 miners were killed in a similar blast. The last
mining accident in Sokobanja occurred in 1975 when a methane
explosion took five lives.
</P>
<P>
The Serbian government declared a day of mourning on Saturday
after the accident. 
</P>
