<HEADLINE> Conference On Ethical, Cultural Progress Closes </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, January 17 (Xinhua) -- Today was the last day of
China's National Conference on Ethical and Cultural Progress in
Beijing, where delegates from across the country discussed work
experiences in that area over the past few years.
</P>
<P>
President Jiang Zemin, the general secretary of the Communist
Party of China (CPC) Central Committee, met with the delegates
during the meeting. Wei Jianxing, a member of the Standing
Committee of the Political Bureau of the CPC Central Committee,
spoke to the delegates.
</P>
<P>
Participants agreed that progress has been made in the past
several years, and decided that, for 1998, ethical and cultural
progress work will be carried out under the leadership of the
Party Central Committee with Jiang Zemin at the core and under the
guidance of Deng Xiaoping Theory.
</P>
<P>
The goals of ethical and cultural progress should be reached so
as to advance the reforms, development, and stability of the
country, the participants agreed, and they are urging local
governments to gain a better understanding of the importance of
ethical and cultural progress and to do better job in this area
this year. 
</P>
</TEXT>
