<HEADLINE> Aid Continues To Come To Earthquake Area In Northern China </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, January 17 (Xinhua) -- Over ten million yuan in relief
funds has been provided to Zhangjiakou in northern China's Hebei
Province as of this morning, in addition to relief goods.
</P>
<P>
Zhangjiakou was hit by a magnitude 6.2 earthquake at 11:50 am
(Beijing time) on January 10, leaving 49 people dead, over 2,000
injured, and over 136,000 houses damaged.
</P>
<P>
Sources from the Red Cross Society of Tianjin, the northern
Chinese port city, said that it has received 3.5 million yuan in
donations from individuals and enterprises there.
</P>
<P>
About one million yuan worth of coats, quilts, and shoes
contained in twenty trunks was transported to Zhangjiakou this
afternoon, and the General Logistics Department of the People's
Liberation Army donated more relief funds.  
</P>
</TEXT>
