<HEADLINE> China Cracks Down On Illegal Cigarette Business </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, January 17 (Xinhua) -- In 1997, Chinese authorities
made considerable progress in cracking down on the production and
sale of fake cigarette, and the smuggling of contraband cigarettes
from abroad.
</P>
<P>
Local administrations, with the help of other government
departments, confiscated 230,000 cases of contraband cigarettes
and 473,000 cases of cigarettes with faked brand names.
</P>
<P>
They also closed down 684 illegal cigarette workshops,
confiscated 2,400 pieces of equipment, and closed 79 unauthorized
cigarette wholesale markets. 
</P>
</TEXT>
