<HEADLINE> 340 Ugandans Die of Cholera Since Outbreak </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
KAMPALA, January 17 (Xinhua) -- A total of 340 people in
Uganda have died of cholera since its outbreak in late November,
The New Vision reported today.
</P>
<P>
The epidemic has affected 21 of the country's 45 districts,
said Sam Okware, chairman of the national cholera task force on
Friday.
</P>
<P>
In a related development, the health ministry instructed
district health officials to check schools to ensure they have
adequate sanitation facilities before opening for the first term
of the new academic year in January.
</P>
<P>
Crispus Kiyonga, the Minister of Health, said last week in
eastern city of Mbale that schools may not open unless district
medical officials properly assess them.
</P>
<P>
The epidemic is on its decrease, Okware added. The number of
cholera cases in the capital of Kampala has reduced from 150 to
75 a day. In Mbale, the most hit up-country district, daily
cholera cases have been reduced from 80 to 20. 
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
