<HEADLINE> Hungary Seeks to Improve Ties with Nigeria </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
LAGOS, January 17 (Xinhua) -- Hungary has expressed readiness
to offer Nigeria the service of medical doctors as part of a
renewed drive to improve bilateral relations between the two
countries, the Daily Times reported today.
</P>
<P>
The Hungarian government is desirous of exploring new areas of
collaboration with Nigeria and consolidating existing bilateral
agreements, Hungarian Ambassador James Balassa told Nigerian
Health Minister Rear Admiral Jubril Ayinla in the capital Abuja
on Friday.
</P>
<P>
Noting the decline in trade between the two countries in the
last few years, the envoy stressed that it would be beneficial to
both sides to make efforts to extend the frontiers of
collaboration.
</P>
<P>
Balasssa also stated that the health sector was one area with
a lot of potentials for growth, adding that apart from medical
doctors, Hungarian pharmaceutical companies were also eager to
invest in Nigeria. 
</P>
</TEXT>
