<HEADLINE> Party For Non-Communist, Noted Figures Held In Beijing </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, January 17 (Xinhua) -- A non-Communist group of
scholars and prominent figures attended a Spring Festival
party to celebrate the traditional Chinese Lunar New Year
that falls on January 28.
</P>
<P>
The gathering was sponsored by the United Front Department
(UFD) of the Communist Party of China (CPC) Central
Committee. Vice-Chairman of the Chinese People's Political
Consultative Conference National Committee Wang Zhaoguo, who is
the head of the UFD, addressed the party and sent holiday
greetings to all non-Communist intellectuals across the country.
</P>
<P>
Wang pledged to continue to implement the CPC's policy and
principles for non-Communist intellectuals, and to continue to
increase ties with them.
</P>
<P>
The departments will work to solve problems and difficulties
that non-Communist intellectuals encounter in their work and lives.
</P>
<P>
Also present at the gathering were vice-chairmen of the
National People's Congress Standing Committee Lu Jiaxi and Wu
Jieping. 
