<DOCNO> XIE19980117.0085 </DOCNO>
<DATE_TIME> 1998-01-17 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Hong Kong Connecting to Information Age </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
HONG KONG, January 17 (Xinhua) -- Hong Kong has tremendous
opportunities to develop and put information technology into wide
use to ensure its continued success in the next century, it is
learned from a symposium held here on Saturday.
</P>
<P>
More than 100 professionals from the information technology
sector gathered here Saturday to share their insights into the
opportunities Hong Kong is faced with while it is marching into
the information age of the 21st century.
</P>
<P>
Addressing the seminar "The Opportunities Arising from the
Information Age," keynote speaker Dr. James Lau pointed out: "It
is the right time and right opportunity for Hong Kong to develop
information technology, and Hong Kong is the right place and in
the right position."
</P>
<P>
Dr. Lau, chief executive officer of Hong Kong Industrial
Technology Center Corporation, summed up the city's advantages in
employing information technology -- the strong application
culture, a huge mainland market, a capital raising center,
talents, and the favorable policy by the Hong Kong Special
Administrative Region (HKSAR) government.
</P>
<P>
The HKSAR's Chief Executive, Tung Chee Hwa, in his inaugural
policy address last October, put emphasis on information
technology, which he said is the tool that will shape the 21st
century.
</P>
<P>
In a chapter titled "Connecting to the Information Age," Tung
said: "...the uses to which we are putting information technology
today in Hong Kong are only a foretaste of what will be possible."
He pledged to make Hong Kong a leader, not a follower, in the
information world of tomorrow.
</P>
<P>
Another keynote speaker at today's forum, To Cheuk Wah, an
entrepreneur of a Hong Kong-based high-tech company, told the
participants: "Recruiting the best and the brightest talents is
the key to the information age." One of Hong Kong's advantages is
that it can continue to attract the best experts and professionals
in the field.
</P>
<P>
Other speakers shared their views on how to apply the new
technology more efficiently and widely in all different sectors
ranging from business to public services and personal life.
</P>
<P>
Today's seminar was part of a series of events under the "Hong
Kong -- Connecting with the Information Age" campaign, organized
by Hongkong Telecom, Hong Kong's leading supplier of
telecommunications services. 
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
