<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Germany Wins Women's 4x200m Freestyle Relay </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
PERTH, January 17 (Xinhua) -- Germany held off a late charge by
the United States to win the women's 4x200m freestyle relay at the
world swimming championships here on Saturday.
</P>
<P>
The German quartet, paced by 200m world record holder Franziska
van Almisick, timed eight minutes 1.46 seconds for the gold medal.
</P>
<P>
The American team clocked 8:02.88 to snatch the silver medal
while Australia finished a distant third in 8:04.19.
</P>
<P>
Canada placed fourth in 8:05.59. 
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
