<DATE_TIME> 1998-01-17 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Guangdong-HK-Macao Seminar on Hazardous Weather Closes in HK </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
HONG KONG, January 17 (Xinhua) -- Guangdong, Hong Kong and
Macao held their 12th annual seminar on hazardous weather which
closed here on Saturday.
</P>
<P>
Hosted by Lam Hung-kwan, director of the Hong Kong Observatory,
the two-day meeting focused on the effect of El Nino on the
weather pattern in southern China and selected hazardous weather
cases experienced in 1997.
</P>
<P>
The three parties also took the occasion to consolidate the
arrangement relating to the South China Sea Monsoon experiment and
the South China Rainstorm experiment to be carried out this
summer.
</P>
<P>
The South China Sea Monsoon experiment, an cooperative
scientific project involving many countries and endorsed by the
World Meteorological Organization, is to study the weather systems
associated with the southwest monsoon affecting the East Asia
region in spring and summer every year.
</P>
<P>
The South China Rainstorm experiment is a joint project
involving China's southern provinces and Hong Kong and Macao. It
focuses on the mesoscale rainstorm systems embedded within the
southwest monsoon and the monsoon troughs.
</P>
<P>
The annual seminar is held in turn in Guangzhou, Hong Kong and
Macao. The next seminar will be held in Macao. 
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
</DOC>
