<DATE_TIME> 1998-01-17 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Shanghai's Pudong New Area Flourishing </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
SHANGHAI, January 17 (Xinhua) -- Latest statistics for
Shanghai's Pudong New Area show a GDP of 60.8 billion yuan for
last year, up 18.2 percent from the previous year.
</P>
<P>
The area, where flexible policies are being pursued to
encourage investors, had spent about 50 billion yuan on fixed
assets by the end of last year, an increase of 26 percent from
1996.
</P>
<P>
The area finished a number of infrastructure projects last
year, including a 100,000-sq m green patch in its central part
and the Xupu Bridge that connects Pudong with the Xuhui District
in downtown Shanghai.
</P>
<P>
Work on the Pudong International Airport and the Pudong Section
of the second Shanghai metro line is also going well.
</P>
<P>
About 20 overseas banks and insurance companies have moved
their offices to Pudong, and 9 overseas banks have obtained
approval from the China's central bank to do business in Chinese
currency called yuan.
</P>
<P>
Pudong will open wider to domestic and overseas investors in
the next three years, and spend a great deal improving its
investment environment and tap its potential. 
</P>
</TEXT>
