<HEADLINE> 54 More Kenyans Die of Cholera </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
NAIROBI, January 17 (Xinhua) -- A fresh cholera outbreak in
Busia and Kwale in western Kenya has claimed 54 lives in the past
two weeks, the Daily Nation newspaper reported today.
</P>
<P>
As many as 500 cholera patients in critical condition are
admitted to the local hospital in Busia District, Dr. Seth
Lifede, the Busia medical officer of health, was quoted as
saying.
</P>
<P>
It is difficult to control the outbreak of the epidemic in
Budalangi in the district due to the current floods and failure
by residents to observe hygiene, he said.
</P>
<P>
However, the medical team was working round-the-clock to
ensure the disease do not spread to other parts of the district,
the doctor added.
</P>
<P>
Meanwhile, operations at the Busia District Hospital are still
paralyzed as none of the institution's 185 striking nurses has
reported to work.
</P>
<P>
Experts again appealed to the public to boil water before use
for domestic consumption and observe strict hygienic standards to
help curb the epidemic. 
</P>
</TEXT>
