<HEADLINE> Chiluba Calls for Intensified Battle Against </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
LUSAKA, January 17 (Xinhua) -- Zambian President Frederick
Chiluba has called for an intensified battle against countrywide
poverty, saying there is no liberty nor freedom in poverty, Times
of Zambia reported today.
</P>
<P>
Speaking in parliament Friday, Chiluba said his government is
determined to change Zambia for the better by fighting to
eradicate poverty.
</P>
<P>
There is no growth in an atmosphere of pervasive poverty
unless poverty was fought through responsible citizenship and
commitment, said the president.
</P>
<P>
However, Chiluba added that development is not an overnight
event but an incremental process that takes time and effort and a
clear vision.
</P>
<P>
Chiluba also stressed the role of education, particularly in
economic and social development, saying without education, the
younger generation would not play their role as responsible
citizens and be able to contribute fully to the development of
the country.
</P>
<P>
The head of state challenged members of parliament to take a
keen interest in the education boards to arbitrate between the
competing and partisan interests of educators on the one hand and
policy makers on the other.
</P>
<P>
There is need to urgently resolve the conflicts that are
threatening the education system, he noted. 
</P>
