<HEADLINE> Brazilian Water Polo Player Tests Positive </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
PERTH, January 17 (Xinhua) -- Water polo player Raddi Daniela
from Brazil tested positive for banned drugs in an
out-of-competition doping check, the world swimming ruling body
FINA announced in a short press release on Saturday.
</P>
<P>
The press release said that Daniela tested positive for the
banned substances d,l-amphetamine and hydrochlorthazide.
</P>
<P>
The sample was collected on January 14 and the analysis was
made at the IOC-sanctioned laboratory in Sydney, according to the
press release.
</P>
<P>
The FINA Executive, in their meeting held early Saturday,
decided to suspend Daniela until a hearing can be made following
the test of the B sample, the press release said.
</P>
<P>
If the analysis of the B sample comfirms the positive result,
the case will be forwarded to the FINA Doping Panel and the
Brazilian water polo team will be disqualified from this event,
the press release added. 
</P>
</TEXT>
