<HEADLINE> 58,000 Voters Registration Forms Received in HK </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
HONG KONG, January 17 (Xinhua) -- About 580,000 voter
registration forms have been received by the deadline at midnight
on Friday for geographical constituencies for the 1998 Legislative
Council elections.
</P>
<P>
A statement issued by the Registration and Electoral Office on
Saturday said it was estimated that some half of the forms are
from new electors. The remaining forms are mainly reports of
change in residential addresses from people already on the
electoral roll, the statement said.
</P>
<P>
Registration figures for functional constituencies and the
Election Committee subsectors will be faxed upon individual
request as soon as they are available, according to the statement.
</P>
</TEXT>
