<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Hong Kong to Launch Influenza Vaccination Program </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
HONG KONG, January 17 (Xinhua) -- Hong Kong's Department of
Health (DH) will launch an influenza vaccination program next
month to cover some 40,000 residents of all the 600 elderly homes
in Hong Kong, it was announced here on Saturday.
</P>
<P>
In collaboration with the Social Welfare Department and
non-governmental organizations (NGOs) in the subvented sector, the
program is scheduled to start on February 2 and complete within
the month in time before the next influenza peak is expected to
set in around March.
</P>
<P>
The vaccination to boost overall immunity among the elderly
will be done by DH vaccination teams and nursing staff of elderly
homes.
</P>
<P>
The decision came after the Advisory Committee on Immunization
(ACI) endorsed the recommendation at an October 1997 meeting, a
department spokesman said. 
</P>
</TEXT>
