<HEADLINE> Pak-China Relations Time-tested: Minister </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
ISLAMABAD, January 17 (Xinhua) -- Pakistani Information
Minister Mushahid Hussain said here on Saturday Pakistan and China
enjoy special and time-tested relations which are role model for
the entire world.
</P>
<P>
Talking to a six-member delegation of the Communist Party of
China (CPC) led by Vice Minister Ma Wenpu, Mushahid said Islamabad
is grateful to Beijing for its support in times of test and on
issues pertaining to Pakistan's national security and economy.
</P>
<P>
"Pak-China friendship has not grown in greenhouse but it stood
trial and turbulence," he said, "it can be named as model
relationship between two neighbors."
</P>
<P>
Mushahid said Pakistan would never forget China's assistance
without attaching any political strings and conditions.
</P>
<P>
He said China, being a large country, has had good and friendly
relations with all its small neighbors and has never interfered in
internal affairs of other countries including Pakistan.
</P>
<P>
The Information Minister greeted China on the peaceful return
of Hong Kong and termed it "victory for justice, human rights and
international law."
</P>
<P>
He reiterated Islamabad's unflinching support to Beijing on its
position on the question of Taiwan, on so-called human rights
issue and on China's policies for preserving protecting its
territorial integrity against any foreign intervention.
</P>
<P>
The Chinese delegation leader Ma Wenpu said in the meeting
Pakistan and China had all-weathered relations which remained
unaffected throughout the past decades.
</P>
<P>
Ma stressed the need for further strengthening of the
traditional ties between the two countries.
</P>
<P>
He also stressed the need for enhancing interaction between CPC
and the ruling Pakistan Muslim League (N).
</P>
<P>
The visit of the Chinese delegation is aimed at promoting
mutual understanding and friendship between the people and ruling
parties of the two countries, Ma said.  
</P>
</TEXT>
