<HEADLINE> World Cup Downhills Called off by Snow </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
VIENNA, January 17 (Xinhua) -- Heavy snow overnight forced a
women's Alpine skiing World Cup downhill to be postponed in
Altenmarkt, Austria, on Saturday while the start of a men's race
in Wengen, Switzerland, was delayed.
</P>
<P>
Organisers said the Altenmarkt race would be held on Sunday
together with a women's super-G if weather permitting. The start
of the men's downhill in Switzerland was pushed back to 1230 GMT
because of snow and poor visibility.
</P>
<P>
The Altenmarkt downhill has been rescheduled for Sunday at 0815
GMT and the super-G at 1130 GMT on the 2,560 meters long
Kaelberloch piste.
</P>
<P>
The women's races, which had originally been scheduled for
Kitzbuehel, had to be moved to Altenmarkt due to a lack of
snow. 
</P>
