<HEADLINE> US Defense Secretary Arrives in Beijing </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, January 17 (Xinhua) -- US Secretary of the Department
of Defense William Cohen arrived in Beijing this evening on a
three-day official visit to China.
</P>
<P>
Cohen is the fifth incumbent US defense secretary who has
visited China since the two countries established diplomatic
relations in January 1979. He is also the first US cabinet member
who has come to China since Chinese President Jiang Zemin visited
the United States in last October.
</P>
<P>
Cohen is leading a 57-member delegation from the United States
to China at the invitation of Chi Haotian, vice-chairman of the
Central Military Commission (CMC), state councillor and defense
minister.
</P>
<P>
Xiong Guangkai, deputy chief of the General Staff of the
Chinese People's Liberation Army (PLA), and US Ambassador to China
James Sasser greeted Cohen and his entourage at the airport.
