<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Russian Veteran Wins Women's 1m Springboard </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
PERTH, January 17 (Xinhua) -- Russian veteran Irina Lashiko
topped her career with a convincing victory at the women's 1m
springboard diving final of the world swimming championships on
Saturday.
</P>
<P>
The 24-year-old Lashiko, 3m springboard runner-up to Chinese
diving queen Fu Mingxia at the 1996 Olympic Games, collected a
winning total of 296.07 points from the five-dive final, beating
her teammate Vera Ilyina into second place.
</P>
<P>
Ilyina, who defeated Lashiko to win the European championship
title last year, garnered 288.06 points.
</P>
<P>
Chinese Zhang Jing, whose performance was getting worse as the
competition went on, scored 260.31 points for the bronze medal.
Her teammate Rao Lang finished last sixth in the final.
</P>
<P>
Switzerland's Jackie Schneider placed fifth with 259.77 points
and Canadian Eryn Bulmer was fifth with 257.01. 
</P>
</TEXT>
