<P>
UNITED NATIONS -- The United Nations has told its weapons
inspection team led by American Scott Ritter to pull out of Iraq,
UN spokesman Fred Eckhard said at Thursday's noon briefing.
</P>
<P>
"The team has been told to leave the country and return to
their home base," Fred said.
</P>
<P>
Iraq has prevented the weapon inspectors led by American Scott
Ritter from operating since Tuesday, saying the team is dominated
by Americans and Britons, and accused Ritter spying for the United
States. (UN Team-Iraq-Leave)
</P>
