<HEADLINE> Rios Claims BellSouth Open Title </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
WELLINGTON, January 17 (Xinhua) -- Marcelo Rios of Chile
rallied back from a set down to win the final of the BellSouth
Open tennis tournament in Auckland, New Zealand, on Saturday.
</P>
<P>
The top seed and world No.10 scored a 4-6, 6-4, 7-6 (7-3)
victory against Australian Richard Fromberg.
</P>
<P>
Fromberg, who served 10 aces in the match, earned three break
points in the 10th game to take the first set.
</P>
<P>
But he ruined his 3-1 lead in the second set when Rios, urged
on by a vocal band of supporters, broke back in the next game to
take the sting out of the Australian's fight.
</P>
<P>
Rios, after going ahead 4-3 with serve in the tiebreak in the
third set, broke Fromberg's serve twice to lead 6-3 then wasted no
time in taking the match-winning point with his next serve to seal
the match in victory. 
</P>
