<HEADLINE> Christensen Beats Arbi To Reach The Final </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
TOKYO, January 17 (Xinhua) -- Top seeded Peter Gade Christensen
of Denmark edged Indonesian star Heryanto Arbi in their first
clash to secure a place in the final of the Yonex Japan Open
badminton tournament here on Saturday.
</P>
<P>
The Dane was one game and 0-2 down when he started hitting a
series of effective short serves to chalk up point after point and
shifted the momentum in his favour to win 4-15, 15-2, 15-6.
</P>
<P>
Arbi, the champion here in 1993 ad 1995, was quicker than
Christensen at the net, winning some clean points with his attacks
in the first game.
</P>
<P>
But Christensen's short serves surprisingly caused numerous
errors to Arbi's service return and the 21-year-old Dane won 15
points in a row to tie the contest at one game all.
</P>
<P>
In the men's singles final Sunday, Christensen will take on Luo
Yigang of China, who beat Atlanta Olympic bronze medallist Rasid
Sidek of Malaysia 15-17, 15-7, 15-4.
</P>
<P>
In the women's semifinals which featured four Chinese players,
top seed Ye Zhaoying defeated Dai Yun 11-1, 11-9 while
second-seeded Gong Zhichao eliminated Wang Chen 11-3, 11-5.
</P>
