<HEADLINE> Sri Lankan Air Force Destroys LTTE Base: Spokesman </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
COLOMBO, January 17 (Xinhua) -- Two ground attack aircraft of
the Sri Lankan Air Force Friday bombed and destroyed a fortified
base of the Liberation Tigers of Tamil Eelam (LTTE) in the north,
Military Spokesman R.P. Vitana said Saturday.
</P>
<P>
The attack took place near Mallavi in the Northern jungles at
Friday noon.
</P>
<P>
The base caught fire as a result of the bombing. Pilots of the
attacker planes said they observed thick black smoke billowing up
with dense flames, which indicated there could have been an oil
dump or ammunition store in the well-camouflaged semi-permanent
structures.
</P>
<P>
Vitana said rebel vehicles rushed in to evacuate the dead and
the injured following the attack. Casualties and damages of the
base are not available yet.
</P>
<P>
Government troops in Operation Jayasikuru (Certain Victory) are
conducting small group operations against the LTTE in the region.
</P>
<P>
The operation has been going on for more than eight months and
there is still no sign of ending it in the near future.
</P>
<P>
The major objective of the operation is to capture a land route
running to the north from rebel hands.  
</P>
</TEXT>
