<DATE_TIME> 1998-01-17 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Kazak President Pledges to Build a Modern Army </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
ALMA-ATA, January 16 (Xinhua) -- Kazakhstan should build its
army into a highly capable, efficient, professional and
well-equipped armed force, Kazak President Nursultan Nazarbayev
said here Friday.
</P>
<P>
Nazarbayev made the remark while inspecting the Kazak College
for Armed Forces.
</P>
<P>
He was quoted by the Kazak Telegraph Agency as saying
Kazakhstan is intensifying its efforts to construct a new
defensive military theory and a military reform framework will be
conceived by the year 2000.
</P>
<P>
He said, with the growth of the national economy, the armed
forces will be able to receive sufficient funds for equipment and
technological innovation from 2000 to 2003.
</P>
<P>
The president said his country is currently working on an
outline for development of arms and military technology before the
year 2005, which involves separating the functions of the
department of defense and the army staff.
</P>
<P>
He said measures will soon be taken to reinforce the public
surveillance over the armed forces, which is an indispensable step
in safeguarding the legal system and order inside the army.
</P>
<P>
The people, he said, have the right to know the spending of the
national budgetary funds and the performance of their children in
service.
</P>
<P>
Nazarbayev expressed his dissatisfaction over the lack of
discipline and order within the army. The offenses recorded by the
Military Procuratorate last year increased by 7.6 percent over the
previous year to more than 1,800. There were also serious abuses
of power.
</P>
<P>
He asked the officers at all levels to be responsible for the
army's combat readiness and moral conduct.
</P>
<P>
The Kazak College for Armed Forces was founded on the basis of
the Alma-Ata Advanced Military School a year ago.
</P>
<P>
In the past 20 years, the school has trained about 7,000
officers, and nearly 1,000 have graduated since the independence
of Kazakhstan. 
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
