<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Kucera Upsets Heman in Sydney Final </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
CANBERRA, January 17 (Xinhua) -- Slovakian Karol Kucera came
from behind to upset No. 1 seed Tim Henman of Britain 7-5, 6-4 in
the final of the Sydney International on Saturday.
</P>
<P>
Kucera, ranked 25th in the world, won four straight games to
tie the set at 4-4 after Henman broke the Slovakian's first two
service games to take a 4-0 lead, and then broke in the 11th game
for 6-5.
</P>
<P>
The unseeded Kucera then held the 11th game, finishing on an
ace to take the set 7-5.
</P>
<P>
Kucera's comeback in the first set appeared to demoralise
Henman and he kept his winning momentum to finish the second set
6-4, leaving the British 17th in the world stranded.
</P>
<P>
In Women's final, Spanish fifth seed Arantxa Sanchez Vicario
downed American teenager Venus Williams 6-1, 6-3 for the title.
</P>
<P>
Venus worked hard against her more experienced competitor, but
her every error was exploited.
</P>
<P>
"I think she is one of the players who is very consistent and
waits on you to make a mistake," Williams was quoted as
saying. "I'm more of a high-risk player."  
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
