<HEADLINE> Bangladesh to Publish National Encyclopedia </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
DHAKA, January (Xinhua) -- The Asiatic Society of Bangladesh
(ASB) has initiated a five-year project to publish a national
encyclopedia for the first time in the country, the ASB said
Saturday.
</P>
<P>
The ASB has received commitments from national and
international organizations regarding financial support of the
project, which will cost an estimated 100 million taka (2.22
million U.S. dollars).
</P>
<P>
Sirajul Islam, professor of history at the University of Dhaka
and a member of the Royal History Society has been appointed chief
editor and director of the encyclopedia project, the ASB said.
</P>
<P>
The Bangladesh Encyclopedia will be compiled in 10 volumes in
both English and Bengali, and is expected to contain a minimum of
10,000 entries contributed by more than 1,000 scholars from both
home and abroad. 
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
