<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Philippoussis Downs Agassi in Australian Open Warm-up </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
CANBERRA, January 17 (Xinhua) -- Australia's Mark Philippoussis
aced his way past former world number one Andre Agassi to win the
Kooyong Classic final in Melbourne on Saturday.
</P>
<P>
Philippoussis, 21, fired down 21 aces to wrap up the title 6-3,
7-6 (7/3) in 67 minutes and expose gaps in Agassi's comeback
campaign.
</P>
<P>
Agassi, the 27-year-old American, lost his serve in the fifth
game by hitting out a simple volley over the net when his opponent
was nowhere in sight.
</P>
<P>
Philippoussis lived up to his nickname "scud" by hittng his
serve with a 200 kilometers an hour ace.
</P>
<P>
After taking the Colonial Classic title, Philippoussis, who had
been overtaken by Australia's number one Pat Rafter, said he had
been "working quietly while the limelight had turned to
fellow-Australian Rafter".
</P>
<P>
Althoug Agassi lost the tune-up for Australian Open, he still
insisted he was fully prepared for the Australian Open, which he
won in 1995. 
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
