<BODY>
<HEADLINE> China's Jiangxi to Ensure Grand Program for New Products </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
NANCHANG, January 17 (Xinhua) -- East China's Jiangxi Province
will this year implement a grand program to develop new products
and import foreign funds and technology.
</P>
<P>
The program involves a total investment of 7.55 billion yuan,
according to an official figure.
</P>
<P>
Under the program, Jiangxi will develop and trial-produce 1,000
new products and make an intense effort to ensure the development
of large enterprise groups with sales of more than one billion
yuan and gross profits exceeding 100 million yuan each, Governor
Shu Shengyou revealed in a recent report.
</P>
<P>
The program will focus on the development of such industries as
automobile, machinery, information, pottery, medicine,
electronics, food, textile, metallurgy, construction materials and
chemistry.
</P>
<P>
The eastern Chinese province's strategy for the development of
brand-name products, started in 1995, has laid a solid foundation
for the implementation of the new-product program, an expert said.
</P>
<P>
Official data show that Jiangxi had 95 provincial-grade
brandnames by the end of last year. 
</P>
</TEXT>
