<TEXT>
<P>
NAIROBI, January 17 (Xinhua) -- The following are major news
items in leading Kenyan newspapers today.
</P>
<P>
Kenya Times
</P>
<P>
--The Nairobi-Mombasa highway, also known as the Trans-Africa
highway, was Friday closed down indefinitely after a 30-kilometer
stretch was cut off due to the raging El Nino floods.
</P>
<P>
Daily Nation
</P>
<P>
-- Tanzania's ruling party and the Opposition have both
rejected proposals by Commonwealth Secretary-General Chief Emeka
Anyaoku to resolve their heated political differences over
Zanzibar.
</P>
<P>
-- At least two civilians were killed in Burundi when armed
gunmen ambushed a bus outside the capital of Bujumbura, an army
spokesman said Friday.
</P>
<P>
East African Standard
</P>
<P>
-- Cholera toll continued to rise with deaths being reported
in various parts of Kenya.
</P>
<P>
-- Heavily-armed soldiers raided the offices of an opposition
newspaper in Malawi, beating up staff and wrecking equipment in
anger over a report about AIDS in the army. 
</P>
