<HEADLINE> Yunnan Tourism Company To Issue Shares in Hong Kong </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
KUNMING, January 17 (Xinhua) -- Yunnan Tourism Group Co. Ltd of
southwest China's Yunnan Province will list H shares in Hong Kong
in the near future, according to the provincial tourism
administration.
</P>
<P>
The listing has been approved by the China Securities
Regulatory Committee.
</P>
<P>
Investment banks and financial companies from Hong Kong and
Japan are currently making preparation for the share listing,
which is expected to rake in funds worth 1.2 billion Hong Kong
dollars.
</P>
<P>
The tourism group is one of the 38 candidate enterprises
selected by the State Council for overseas listing in 1996. It
owns four enterprise in administration of tourist attractions, one
travel agency, three starred hotels, and a transportation
enterprise. The total assets of the group company have been
estimated at more than 700 million yuan and annual net profit
about 100 million yuan.
</P>
<P>
The funds raised through the planned listing will be used to
develop tourist spots, including the expansion of a stone forest
park and the building of a skiing ground.
</P>
<P>
Official figures show that the tourism industry of Yunnan has
been growing at an annual rate of over 30 percent in recent
years. More than 800,000 overseas people and 20 million Chinese
visited Yunnan last year, with the province's tourism revenue
exceeded 10 billion yuan. 
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
