<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Guangdong Accelerates Legislative Efforts </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
GUANGZHOU, January 17 (Xinhua) -- South China's Guangdong
Province has accelerated legislative efforts over the past few
years in order to strengthen laws and ensure smooth economic
development.
</P>
<P>
Statistics show that the economically prosperous province has
formulated and approved 151 local regulations since 1993, with
some 65 percent of them involving economic management, the
environment, the protection of resources and scientific
development.
</P>
<P>
Guangdong, the vanguard of China's reform and opening drive,
has consistently remained one step ahead of other inland provinces
in tackling new problems resulting from rapid economic development.
</P>
<P>
According to a local official, "Guangdong leads the country in
legislative efforts and experimentation in wide-ranging fields."
</P>
<P>
He said the province has done a good job in formulating
regulations governing economic behavior, bidding for construction
projects and real estate management.
</P>
<P>
By the end of 1997, the province had amended 55 regulations and
abolished nine regulations in a move to adapt to the needs of
economic development.  
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
