<DATE_TIME> 1998-01-17 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Weekly Report on Kuala Lumpur Stock Market </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
KUALA LUMPUR, January 17 (Xinhua) -- Share prices on the Kuala
Lumpur Stock Exchange (KLSE) staged a strong recovery this week
with the Composite Index rebounding to above the 500-point level.
</P>
<P>
The Composite Index surged 48.34 points or 9.83 percent to end
the week at 539.94.
</P>
<P>
The all Main Board share EMAS Index closed at 137.19, up 10.42
points or 8.22 percent and the Industrial Index added 65.9 points
or 6.48 percent to reach 1,082.65.
</P>
<P>
The Second Board Index, which normally reflects punters'
interest, soared 25.69 points or 20.16 percent to close at 153.11.
</P>
<P>
The market rallied as foreign players as well as local players
are making a comeback and because the local currency, the
ringgit, recovered to end the week at 4.17 to the U.S. dollar from
4.56 last week.
</P>
<P>
This week's top 10 active stocks included United Engineers Bhd
and Renong Bhd which were quoted on Wednesday and both counters
tumbled as investors were cool toward their cross-holding
strategy.
</P>
<P>
The other eight top active counters were Sime Darby, Tenaga
Nasional, IOI, Magnum, Berjaya Group, Commerce-Asset, RHB Capital
and MBF Capital, and they were all up.
</P>
<P>
The weekly Main Board ready turnover expanded to 1.036 billion
shares worth 2.235 billion ringgit (about 532.14 million U.S.
dollars) from 692.014 million shares valued at 1.633 billion
ringgit (about 388.8 million dollars) last week.
</P>
<P>
The Second Board turnover increased to 170.683 million shares
worth 312.254 million ringgit (about 74.34 million dollars) from
56.335 million shares valued at 109.37 million ringgit (about
26.04 million dollars).
</P>
<P>
Direct businesses amounted to 47.91 million shares worth
164.092 million ringgit (about 39.07 million dollars) from 55.184
million shares valued at 226.272 million ringgit (about 53.87
million dollars) last week.
</P>
<P>
On the Main Board, consumer products accounted for 53.383
million shares traded, industrial products 73.417 million shares,
construction 203.682 million shares, trading/services 264.762
million shares and infrastructure 5.634 million shares. Meanwhile,
Finance took up 161.817 million shares, hotels 6.261 million
shares, properties 90.65 million shares, plantation 78.045 million
shares, mining 9.307 million shares, trusts 1.412 million shares,
closed-end funds 1.188 million shares, loan stocks 35.897 million
shares, TSR/warrants 45.316 million shares and rights 5.631
million shares.  
</P>
</TEXT>
