<TEXT>
<P>
YANGON, January 17 (Xinhua) -- Myanmar has worked out plans for
reducing crime in the country and urged writers and artists to
play a role in the bid.
</P>
<P>
At a meeting with local writers and artists Friday, Minister
for Home Affairs Tin Hlaing briefed them on the plans for reducing
crime and called on the participants to provide assistance to the
move, the New Light of Myanmar reported Saturday.
</P>
