<DATE_TIME> 1998-01-17 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Indonesia's Foreign Assets Total US$20.39 Billion </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
JAKARTA, January 17 (Xinhua) -- Bank Indonesia, the country's
central bank, announced Friday that the country's gross foreign
assets totaled 20.39 billion U.S. dollars as of January 15 this
year, down from 27.56 billion dollars as of last September.
</P>
<P>
This was the first time the central bank defined the country's
official foreign reserves as gross foreign assets, or simply
called foreign assets -- the net amount of foreign currency assets
available to the central bank, the local press reported Saturday.
</P>
<P>
Previously the official foreign exchange reserves reported by
the central bank did not include the foreign exchange deposited by
commercial banks as a compulsory foreign exchange reserve
requirement or export drafts, said the reports.
</P>
<P>
Bank Indonesia Director Miranda S. Gultom said in a statement
that the 20.39 billion dollars are the equivalent of the need for
importing non-oil and gas commodities for five months.
</P>
<P>
The gross foreign assets were based on a concept used
internationally in line with the special data dissemination
standards of the International Monetary Fund (IMF) which has been
also applied by the Indonesian government.
</P>
<P>
IMF in its publication, Balance of Payment Manual, says foreign
reserves are gross foreign assets that are available at any time
and controlled by monetary authorities.  
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
</DOC>
<DOC>
<DOCNO> XIE19980117.0177 </DOCNO>
<DATE_TIME> 1998-01-17 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Italian Government Extends Autostrade Concession </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
ROME, January 16 (Xinhua) -- The Italian government decided on
Friday to extend Autostrade SpA's concession to run the national
motor-way network till 2038.
</P>
<P>
The extension of the soon-to-be-privatized Autostrade came in a
decree law issued on Friday despite the Audit Court's objection that
the move ran counter to European Union regulations on free
competition.
</P>
<P>
The decision also overrode the opposition of Environment
Minister Edo Ronchi and drew an angry response from his party, the
Greens.
</P>
<P>
Autostrade, which is due to be privatized this year, at the
moment only has this right until 2018, the 20-year extension has
added considerably to the company's market value.
</P>
<P>
But the Audit Court, which examines every law entailing
government spending for legal hitches, pointed out last year that
under EU free market rules the government could not simply hand
Autostrade SpA a new concession to run Italy's motor-ways.
</P>
<P>
As with all government contracts, the moter-way concession
should be offered after a public tender operation, which allowed
companies from all over the world to bid for it, the court said.
</P>
<P>
By overriding the court's objection, the government lays itself
open to disciplinary measures by the EU, should Brussels decide
the move constitutes a breach of regulations. 
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
</DOC>
