<HEADLINE> Energy Declaration Issued for Americas </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
CARACAS, January 16 (Xinhua) -- Energy ministers of the 26
American countries promised here on Friday that they would join
efforts to promote the integration of regional energy market.
</P>
<P>
They made the promise in the Caracas Declaration issued at the
end of the Third Hemispheric Meeting of Energy Ministers, which
was held here on Thursday.
</P>
<P>
Also in the declaration, the ministers from Venezuela, the
United States and other member states of the Latin America Energy
Organization, committed themselves to promoting the policies and
processes that would help boost the trade of products and services
in the energy sector.
</P>
<P>
They stressed the importance of establishing legal and
financial bases for private, national or foreign investment in the
energy sector.
</P>
<P>
Also at the two-day meeting, the ministers decided to set up a
secretariat to coordinate the efforts defined in the declaration.
</P>
<P>
The next Hemispheric Meeting of Energy Ministers will be held
in Mexico in 1999. 
</P>
