<HEADLINE> Housing Sector to Act as New Catalyst of China's Economic Growth </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, January 17 (Xinhua) -- Yu Zhengsheng, vice-minister of
construction, urged China's builders to construct better houses
and improve after-sales service to encourage people to buy their
own homes, "China Daily" reported today.
</P>
<P>
Addressing a national construction conference which ended here
Friday, Yu said the main task for the construction industry this
year is "to improve the hosing distribution system and fuel
housing consumption spending."
</P>
<P>
Calling residential housing sector a new "catalyst of economic
growth," Yu urged construction officials to "alter some of their
traditional concepts and emancipate their minds" to develop the
sector in line with the market economy.
</P>
<P>
"Construction officials should not interfere in the bidding,
contracting or designing of construction projects. Rather, they
should enhance supervision to ensure a fair and open bidding
atmosphere, and the sound implementation of the new Construction
Law," Yu said.
</P>
<P>
Li Zhendong, another vice-minister of construction, said the
country should make a substantial breakthrough in its housing
distribution system reform this year and stop granting houses as a
kind of welfare benefit.
</P>
<P>
He urged officials in the sector to adapt to the changes,
including bank loans for home construction.
</P>
<P>
Newly built homes in urban areas totaled 300 million sq m, and
those in rural areas amounted to 650 million sq m last year,
ministry statistics indicate.
</P>
<P>
Of the commercial residential houses sold during the
January-November period in 1997, more than 58 percent were
purchased by individuals, a rise of 27.7 percent from the previous
year.  
</P>
</TEXT>
