<TEXT>
<P>
YANGON, January 17 (Xinhua) -- A seminar on analysis and
assessment of the present economic situation in Myanmar is being
held here to study the effect on the country of the current
regional financial crisis.
</P>
<P>
The four-day seminar, which began Friday, is sponsored by the
Office of Strategic Studies (OSS) of the Ministry of Defense and
the Tun Foundation Bank, a private economic institution, the
official newspaper The New Light of Myanmar reported Saturday.
</P>
<P>
It is held with the aim of keeping Myanmar entrepreneurs,
businessmen and government employees well-informed about the
causes that led to the unstable financial situation in the
Southeast Asian region, Myanmar leader Lieutenant-General Khin
Nyunt was quoted as saying.
</P>
<P>
Khin Nyunt, who is first secretary of the Myanmar State Peace
and Development Council and chief of the OSS, said at the opening
session that "Myanmar could also very well suffer from the
backlash of this financial crisis to a greater or lesser extent."
</P>
<P>
He said the government, on its part, is dedicated to carrying
out tasks of national reconstruction and reforms consistent with
the changing times.
</P>
<P>
He called for a more effective role of both scholars and
private entrepreneurs in building Myanmar into a modern and
developed nation.
</P>
<P>
Attending the seminar are local scholars, entrepreneurs and
government departmental officials.  
