<DATE_TIME> 1998-01-17 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Guangxi Investing Heavily in Region's Infrastructure </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
NANNING, January 17 (Xinhua) -- Southwest China's Guangxi
Zhuang Autonomous Region allocated 200 billion yuan for
infrastructure construction and basic industries during the
1993-1997 period.
</P>
<P>
In 1997 the region invested 52.4 billion yuan (6.55 billion
U.S. dollars) in the sectors, said Cheng Kejie, chairman of the
region.
</P>
<P>
Cheng said the region has built 7,738 kilometers of roads in
the period. Two expressways have been completed -- one links
Guilin City, a major tourist site, and Liuzhou City; the other
connects Qinzhou City and Fangchenggang City.
</P>
<P>
The region's three large ports -- Fangchenggang, Beihai and
Qinzhou -- have built 18 wharves with an added annual handling
capacity of 4.86 million tons. The region's coastal ports now have
an annual handling capacity of more than nine million tons, Cheng
said.
</P>
<P>
Twenty-nine wharves have been built along the Xijiang River,
the main stream on the upper reaches of the Pearl River. As a
result, a total of 4.21 million tons of handling capacity has been
added.
</P>
<P>
The region has begun operations of airports at Guilin, Liuzhou
and Wuzhou and have increased capacity at Beihai and Nanning
airports.
</P>
<P>
By the end of 1997 the number of telephone and mobile phone
subscribers had expanded to 2.5 million and 630,000, respectively.
</P>
<P>
During the 1993-97 period, the region built hydropower stations
such as Yantan and Tianshengqiao for an additional installed
capacity of 2.66 million kilowatts.
</P>
<P>
The region also built 1,463 kilometers of 500,000-volt power
transmission lines connecting the region with Guangdong, Yunnan
and Guizhou provinces.
</P>
<P>
Cheng said the region also has added 50,000 hectares of
irrigated farmland in the past five years. 
</P>
</TEXT>
