<HEADLINE> Highlights of Major Beijing-Based Newspapers </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, January 17 (Xinhua) -- The following are highlights of
major Beijing-based newspapers today:
</P>
<P>
"People's Daily"
</P>
<P>
-- Vice-Premier Li Lanqing has called on central and local
government departments to speed up the work of tackling the
housing problem for teachers, especially younger teachers.
</P>
<P>
-- Hu Jintao, a member of the Standing Committee of the
Political Bureau of the Communist Party of China (CPC) Central
Committee and president of the Party School the CPC Central
Committee, handed diplomas to 2,740 graduates of the school at a
ceremony Friday.
</P>
<P>
-- With the Spring Festival approaching, local governments have
been showing great care for needy workers.
</P>
<P>
-- China will continue cracking down on crimes this year,
especially during the upcoming Spring Festival, according to Ren
Jianxin, director of the Central Committee of Comprehensive
Management of Public Security.
</P>
<P>
-- After the earthquakes in Nagqu in Tibet and Zhangjiakou in
Hebei Province, people working at central departments in Beijing
have donated eight million yuan (964,000 US dollars) and more than
700,000 pieces of clothes and quilts.
</P>
