<DOCNO> XIE19980117.0212 </DOCNO>
<DATE_TIME> 1998-01-17 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Hungary's Overseas Investment Grows </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BUDAPEST, January 16 (Xinhua) -- Hungary invested a record 371
million U.S. dollars in other countries in 1997, tripling the 67
million dollars in the previous year.
</P>
<P>
The figures issued by the National Bank of Hungary show that
the bulk of the investment, or 228 million dollars, went to the
Netherlands last year.
</P>
<P>
Hungary's neighboring countries, including Austria and Romania,
shared the remaining part of the total investment.
</P>
<P>
The "NAPI Gazdasag" (World Economy) newspaper Friday attributed
the increased overseas investment to the recovery of the Hungarian
economy, which has enabled many Hungarian companies to expand
their business abroad. 
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
