<DOCNO> XIE19980117.0213 </DOCNO>
<DATE_TIME> 1998-01-17 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Czech Republic, Poland Sign Environment Agreement </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
PRAGUE, January 16 (Xinhua) -- The Czech Republic and Poland
signed an agreement here on Thursday to join their efforts in
environmental protection, the Czech News Agency reported on Friday.
</P>
<P>
The agreement defines the rights and obligations of the two
countries in jointly preventing air and river pollution.
</P>
<P>
The two neighbors also agreed to set up a joint commission on
environmental protection within the next three months to
facilitate their cooperation in this field.
</P>
<P>
The Czech Republic has signed similar agreements with three
other neighboring nations -- Germany, Austria and Slovak. 
</P>
</TEXT>
