<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Italy Olympic Champion Tested Positive for Steroids </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
ROME, January 16 (Xinhua) -- Italian Olympic mountain bike
champion Paola Pezzo was tested positive for steroids, said the
Italian Olympic Committee on Friday.
</P>
<P>
The doping officials decided to submit the world and Olympic
champion for possible disciplinary action, CONI said.
</P>
<P>
Pezzo, 29, faced a ban from six months to one year. A final
decision in the case would be taken by the Italian cycling
federation's disciplinary commission.
</P>
<P>
Pezzo, who became a celebrity in Italy after winning the
Olympic title in Atlanta, said earlier this month she had never
knowingly taken any drug.
</P>
<P>
Pezzo tested positive following a World Cup race in France last
September 6. A later test in December confirmed the result.
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
