<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Canada To Invest More in Argentina </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BUENOS AIRES, January 16 (Xinhua) -- Canadian investment in
Argentina from 1994 to 1997 amounted to 1.185 billion U.S. dollars
and it is expected to reach about 2.5 billion dollars by 2002,
the country's "Invertir" Foundation revealed here on Friday.
</P>
<P>
The Foundation in a report said that the sector that attracted
most investment from Canada during the 1994-1997 period was
mining, with 355.14 million dollars.
</P>
<P>
The sector that will concentrate more investment for this year
will be the Chemical-Pharmaceutical Sector, with 169.5 million
dollars.
</P>
<P>
Canada will be the third foreign investor in Argentina by 2001,
after the United States and Spain, and before France, Germany, and
Chile. 
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
