<DOCNO> XIE19980117.0241 </DOCNO>
<DATE_TIME> 1998-01-17 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Experts: 100,000 Greeks Suffer from Schizophrenia </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
ATHENS, January 16 (Xinhua) -- A total of some 100,000 Greek
people suffer from schizophrenia.
</P>
<P>
The symptoms usually appeared among the patients aged between
between 20-25, Greek experts said, adding that 20 percent of the
patients usually suffered only one episode of the disease during
their lifetime, the semi-official Athens News Agency (ANA)
reported on Friday.
</P>
<P>
They believed that the symptoms usually appeared under the
influence of external factors such as stress.
</P>
<P>
It seems that heredity was involved in the causes of the
disease, as well as illnesses suffered by the mother during
pregancy, such as influenza, the experts said. 
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
