<HEADLINE> UN Arms Team Led by American Pulled out of Iraq </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
UNITED NATIONS, January 16 (Xinhua) -- The United Nations has
told its weapons inspection team led by American Scott Ritter to
pull out of Iraq, UN spokesman Fred Eckhard said at today's noon
briefing.
</P>
<P>
"The team has been told to leave the country and return to
their home base," Fred said.
</P>
<P>
The team, which has been blocked by Iraq from carrying out its
weapons inspection, was originally supposed to leave Iraq on
friday if it could complete its work, the spokesman said.
</P>
<P>
Iraq has prevented the weapon inspectors led by American Scott
Ritter from operating since Tuesday, saying the team is dominated
by Americans and Britons, and accused Ritter spying for the United
states.
</P>
<P>
Richard Butler, the head of the United Nations Special
Commission (UNSCOM) in charge of dismantling Iraq's weapons of
mass destruction, is on his way to visit Baghdad where he is
expected to have talks with Iraqi officials on Monday and Tuesday
on the banning of the team and the right of his inspectors to have
access to all sites.  
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
